<section class="tb-tool-layout" data-controller="image-compress dropzone" data-action="dragover@window->dropzone#over drop@window->image-compress#drop">
  <div>
    <div class="tb-eyebrow">Tool 05</div>
    <h1 class="tb-h1 tb-tool-title">Compress images</h1>
    <p class="tb-text tb-tool-subtitle" style="max-width: 58ch;">
      Drop JPG, PNG or WebP images. We'll shrink them right here in your browser — no upload, no account.
      Nothing leaves your device.
    </p>

    <div class="tb-drop"
         data-image-compress-target="drop"
         data-dropzone-target="zone"
         data-action="click->image-compress#pick dragover->dropzone#over dragleave->dropzone#leave drop->image-compress#drop"
         style="margin-top: 26px;">
      <svg class="tb-drop-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/>
        <circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.5"/>
        <path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="tb-drop-title">Drop images here, or click to choose</div>
      <div class="tb-drop-sub">.jpg · .png · .webp · any number of files · 0 bytes uploaded</div>
    </div>

    <input type="file" accept="image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp" multiple
           data-image-compress-target="input" data-action="change->image-compress#picked" hidden>

    <div data-image-compress-target="options" hidden style="margin-top: 20px; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <div>
        <div class="tb-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Quality</div>
        <div class="tb-tabs" data-image-compress-target="quality">
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setQuality" data-q="0.6">Low 60</button>
          <button class="tb-tab is-active" data-action="click->image-compress#setQuality" data-q="0.8">Med 80</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setQuality" data-q="0.92">High 92</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tb-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Max width</div>
        <div class="tb-tabs" data-image-compress-target="maxdim">
          <button class="tb-tab is-active" data-action="click->image-compress#setMaxDim" data-m="0">Original</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setMaxDim" data-m="2048">2048</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setMaxDim" data-m="1024">1024</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tb-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">Format</div>
        <div class="tb-tabs" data-image-compress-target="format">
          <button class="tb-tab is-active" data-action="click->image-compress#setFormat" data-f="auto">Keep</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setFormat" data-f="image/jpeg">JPG</button>
          <button class="tb-tab" data-action="click->image-compress#setFormat" data-f="image/webp">WebP</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span style="flex: 1;"></span>

      <button class="tb-btn tb-btn-quiet" data-action="click->image-compress#reprocess">Re-compress</button>
      <button class="tb-btn tb-btn-quiet" data-action="click->image-compress#clear">Clear</button>
      <button class="tb-btn tb-btn-primary" data-action="click->image-compress#downloadZip" data-image-compress-target="zipBtn" disabled>
        Download all as .zip
      </button>
    </div>

    <div data-image-compress-target="list" class="tb-card" style="margin-top: 18px; display: none;"></div>
  </div>

  <aside>
    <div class="tb-receipt">
      <div class="tb-receipt-title">
        <span class="tb-receipt-dot"></span>
        <span>Live receipt</span>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-stack-6">
        <div class="tb-receipt-row is-good"><span>bytes sent</span><span data-receipt-target="bytes">0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row is-good"><span>bytes received</span><span>0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>worker</span><span>canvas · toBlob</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>files queued</span><span data-image-compress-target="queued">0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row"><span>files done</span><span data-image-compress-target="done">0</span></div>
        <div class="tb-receipt-row is-good"><span>bytes saved</span><span data-image-compress-target="saved">0</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tb-receipt-foot">
        Canvas re-encoding strips EXIF metadata (that is usually what you want). Transparent PNGs
        compress better when re-saved as WebP.
      </div>
    </div>
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="tb-seo">
  <h2>How do I compress an image online?</h2>
  <p>
    Drop any number of JPG, PNG or WebP files onto the box. Each one is decoded onto an HTML
    <span class="tb-mono">&lt;canvas&gt;</span> in your browser, optionally resized to fit a max dimension,
    then re-encoded at the quality you pick. No network round-trip, no upload, no server-side processing.
  </p>
  <h3>Which format should I pick?</h3>
  <p>
    For photos: JPG at quality 80–90 is usually the sweet spot. If the image has transparency, WebP
    keeps the alpha channel and compresses better than PNG. If your destination (old CMSes, some
    email clients) doesn't support WebP, stick to JPG.
  </p>
  <h3>Does compressing strip EXIF data?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Canvas re-encoding does not preserve metadata, so GPS coordinates, camera model, timestamps
    and colour profiles are stripped. For most people sharing images online, that's a feature.
  </p>
</section>
